nce\")\nax.set_zlabel(\"Lift\")\nax.set_title(\"Rule Strength Space (3D)\")\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.140779Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.142154Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.383071Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.141998Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.38184Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":57},{"id":"90022832-5bef-469b-aac6-6b4df663499c","cell_type":"markdown","source":"This three-dimensional visualization plots each association rule in a multi-metric space where support represents frequency, confidence represents reliability, and lift represents strength, thereby allowing us to observe how strong and rare or frequent different rules are in relation to each other.","metadata":{}},{"id":"a9beb3ac-b3d4-473d-a7be-3ba64e10bf2b","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Rule quality score heatmap","metadata":{}},{"id":"72671731-09b6-403d-aa33-3cbededae6a8","cell_type":"code","source":"\nrules['score'] = rules['lift'] * rules['confidence']\n\ntop = rules.sort_values('score', ascending=False).head(15)\nplt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\nsns.heatmap(\n    top[['support','confidence','lift','score']],\n    annot=True,\n    cmap=\"coolwarm\"\n)\nplt.title(\"Top Rule Quality Heatmap\")\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.384293Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.385781Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.819891Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.385687Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.817283Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x500 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":58},{"id":"d70ec1eb-bb3f-4f40-a183-ed2390b81804","cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Key Takeaways:**\n\n**The standout rule (bright red cell):**\nOne rule has Lift = 3.7 — this is the strongest lift in the entire set.\nThis likely corresponds to the Coke - Sandwich (or similar) rule from your first chart.\n\n**Support is generally low (0.005 – 0.047):**\nMost rules occur in less than 5% of transactions. This is normal in association rule mining — only a few combinations are common.\n\n**Confidence varies widely:**\nRanges from 0.27 to 0.81.\nThe highest confidence (0.81) suggests a very reliable rule (when you buy the first item, you often buy the second).\n\nMost rules have moderate Lift (1.1 – 1.7), except for that one very strong rule at 3.7.","metadata":{}},{"id":"9c03d452-2465-4055-aafc-7a14574b120d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Support vs Confidence","metadata":{}},{"id":"5b720a59-9aeb-4307-afc7-76f400ec7255","cell_type":"code","source":"plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n\nplt.scatter(\n    rules['support'],\n    rules['confidence'],\n    alpha=0.5\n)\n\nplt.xlabel(\"Support\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Confidence\")\nplt.title(\"Support vs Confidence (Rule Distribution)\")\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.820936Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.821242Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.010986Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T11:22:10.821216Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.009633Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":59},{"id":"e3442b4e-b275-43fd-994f-648b7251bfa3","cell_type":"markdown","source":"Most rules are concentrated in the bottom-left corner:\n\n**Low Support** (< 0.02) and Low-to-Medium Confidence.\nThis is very typical — most possible rules are rare and not very reliable.\n\n**High Confidence rules** (0.5 – 0.8):\nThere are several rules with high confidence but relatively low support.\nThese are reliable but infrequent patterns.\n\n**High Support rules:**\nVery few rules have high support (> 0.04). The ones that do tend to have lower confidence.\n\nThe \"sweet spot\" (ideal rules) would be in the top-right area — high support + high confidence. There are only a few points there.","metadata":{}},{"id":"4be5886a-5bc4-4762-8b62-ff55602ba351","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Item Centrality in Association Rule Network","metadata":{}},{"id":"4fa9f375-c75a-4579-b8a2-89556b192715","cell_type":"code","source":"G = nx.Graph()\n\nfor _, row in rules.iterrows():\n    for a in row['antecedents']:\n        for c in row['consequents']:\n            G.add_edge(a, c)\n\ncentrality = nx.degree_centrality(G)\n\ntop = dict(sorted(centrality.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:10])\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n\n# Green bars\nplt.barh(list(top.keys()), list(top.values()), color='#8E80A9')\n\nplt.title(\"Item Centrality in Association Network\")\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.012532Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.012959Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.209351Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.012922Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.207874Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":60},{"id":"82c94bec-249a-4491-8c08-593c2606da3e","cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Business Story:**\n\nCoffee is the hero product. It drives many sales and pairs well with Bread, Tea, Cake, etc.\n\nThere are strong **combo clusters:**\n\n- Coffee / Tea / Bread / Cake (breakfast/snack cluster)\n- Coke / Sandwich (lunch cluster)\n- Cookies / Juice (snack cluster)\n\n**Recommendation:** Focus promotions and menu design heavily around Coffee as the anchor item, while leveraging the strong pairs identified earlier.","metadata":{}},{"id":"e78aec54-d747-418a-9464-66b2826e9243","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Lift Distribution","metadata":{}},{"id":"fb1d5c60-5b07-4e8c-b164-ed7a3f2323ae","cell_type":"code","source":"plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n\n# Histogram of lift values to show rule strength distribution\nplt.hist(rules['lift'], bins=25, color='#7198A9', edgecolor='white')\n\nplt.title(\"Lift Distribution (Rule Strength Overview)\")\nplt.xlabel(\"Lift\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Frequency\")\n\nplt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)\n\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.210724Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.211063Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.433116Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.211029Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.432116Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":61},{"id":"8c38673a-6982-4f61-aa43-da4ec3610aec","cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Key Takeaways:**\n\n- Most rules have weak Lift (0.8–1.3) — common but not useful.\n- Few rules show strong association (Lift > 2.0).\n- Very few exceptional rules (Lift 3.0–3.7), led by Coke - Sandwich.\n- Opportunity lies in the right tail: Focus only on high-Lift rules for maximum impact.\n\n**Bottom line**: Ignore average rules. Prioritize the rare, strong ones for promotions and bundling.","metadata":{}},{"id":"5aeda3ab-3665-456d-aed8-1413a4cb2bb3","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Confidence Distribution","metadata":{}},{"id":"343385ad-1e4f-44c1-8816-b59226f66e82","cell_type":"code","source":"plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n\n# Histogram of lift values to show rule strength distribution\nplt.hist(rules['confidence'], bins=25, color='#7198A9', edgecolor='white')\n\nplt.title(\"Confidence Distribution\")\nplt.xlabel(\"Confidence\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Frequency\")\n\nplt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)\n\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.434421Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.434839Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.645001Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.434803Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T11:22:11.643576Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":62},{"id":"3cc57328-14e5-4884-977a-92e02b12b27a","cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Key Takeaways:**\n- Most rules have low confidence (peak at 0.0–0.1).\n- Sharp drop after 0.2 — high-confidence rules are rare.\n- Small second peak around 0.5–0.6 shows a few reliable rules.\n- Only very few rules exceed 0.7 confidence.\n  \n**Bottom line:** Most associations are unreliable. Focus on the rare high-confidence rules (especially those also with high Lift).","metadata":{}},{"id":"7ebdb232-fb88-4a91-b8f6-6a88ba1f1ea1","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Business Summary","metadata":{}},{"id":"05ef1739-cf86-4187-a6b5-20396b19daa1","cell_type":"markdown","source":"The Apriori analysis identified clear purchasing patterns that can be used to improve product bundling, promotions, and store layout. Bread emerged as the central product, frequently purchased with items such as Coffee, Cake, Cookies, Juice, Brownie, and Hot Chocolate, making it an effective anchor product for cross-selling. Additionally, Coke–Sandwich and Cookies–Juice were the strongest item combinations, indicating natural customer buying habits that can be leveraged through bundled offers.\n\nAlthough most association rules had low support and moderate confidence, a small number exhibited high confidence (up to 0.81) and strong lift (up to 3.7), demonstrating reliable and meaningful purchasing relationships. These high-lift rules represent the greatest business value, while the majority of weaker rules contribute little actionable insight.\n\nOverall, the results suggest that the business should prioritize high-lift, high-confidence product combinations for promotions, meal deals, and shelf placement. Organizing products into customer purchase clusters—such as Breakfast (Bread, Coffee, Cake), Lunch (Coke, Sandwich), and Snacks (Cookies, Juice)—can increase cross-selling opportunities, improve the average basket size, and enhance the overall customer shopping experience.","metadata":{}}]}